<SLUG> BC-VOTING-GROUPS-REVIEW-2TAKES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE MELTING-POT: POLITICS OF 2000 ARE TRULY SOUPY 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
(DUPLICATION NOTICE: Also sent with `a' code) 
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact the Los Angeles office
(Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089) 
(bl) 
 By STEVEN A. HOLMES   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Pity the poor presidential campaign strategists.
With make-or-break primaries fast approaching, they're frantically
trying to cobble together winning strategies to appeal to an
electorate so diverse, cacophonous and in flux as to make the folks
trying to build the Tower of Babel sound like a harmonious glee
