<P>
   DATELINE-INDIA _ President Clinton is coming next month. But, at
the moment, the biggest story in India is about a movie.
Controversial filmmaker Deepa Mehta was set to tackle her latest
sensitive topic here, Hindu widows. She was set to start shooting
her film, which takes place in the 1930s, last week _ until the set
was razed by Hindu nationalists. Now, cultural organizations are
lining up behind Mehta, but the government so far is taking no
steps to protect her. And everyone has an opinion. (Basu, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
