<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   REBEL-FLAG _ The uproar over flying the Confederate battle flag
in South Carolina is playing out in Texas as well. The NAACP wants
the state to ban the flag from public places, particularly public
schools that still use it with their rebel mascot and the Supreme
Court building, with its Confederate plaque. So far, Gov. George W.
Bush and other state leaders have not shown any sign they plan to
follow the group's lead. (Harmon, Austin American-Statesman). 25.
WITH PHOTO. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BLACKHISTORY-YARDDISPLAY _ ATLANTA _ Josie Dean has put up a
yard scene in honor of black history month that has generated quite
a buzz. One woman Friday traveled an hour and a half by bus to see
it; but some neighbors are turning away. Black visitors say Dean is
courageous to depict a lynching scene, but some white neighbors say
it only stirs up pain from a bygone era. (Oglesby, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
