Stevenson Ranch, which borders the Newhall Ranch - the largest
housing development ever approved by Los Angeles County. To its
backers, Newhall Ranch is a sensitively planned community. But
critics point out that much of the demand for housing in the region
is among the growing Hispanic and immigrant populations of urban
Los Angeles, where families are doubled up in apartments and cannot
yet afford suburban houses. (Monica Almeida/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) SANTA CLARITA, CA -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- CALIF-SPRAWL-1 --
The Newhall Ranch development site will border Stevenson Ranch,
Southern California's least populated area. Newhall Ranch is the
largest housing development ever approved by Los Angeles County,
with 21,600 units for 70,000 people to be built over the next 20
years. In that time the local population is expected to double.
(Monica Almeida/The New York Times)
</P>
