Mike Kirkhart, who specializes in models of large saltwater fish,
finishing up a marlin head at New Wave Taxidermy in Stuart. A few
saltwater species have long been reproduced synthetically because
their oily skin deteriorates quickly. But taxidermists now make
replicas of everything from arctic char to piranha to spoonbill
catfish. (Cindy Karp/The New York Times)
</P>
