   (NYT15) NEW YORK -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- CHILE-DECLASSIFY-3 -- Joyce
Horman with her late husband Charles' mother, Elizabeth Horman, 95.
Recently released documents make clear for the first time that the
State Department concluded from almost the beginning that the
Pinochet government had killed both Horman, 31, and Frank Teruggi,
24. Mrs. Horman is hoping she can finally learn what really
happened to her husband and is asking for Washington's help. ``I
want to know who gave the order,'' she says. (Marilynn K. Yee/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) UNDATED -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- CHILE-DECLASSIFY-2 -- Joyce
