away from a government report to reveal more about the deaths of
Charles Horman, left, and Frank Teruggi, center, in Chile in 1973.
American officials categorically denied any role in the young men's
deaths, which were dramatized in the 1982 movie ``Missing.'' (The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) DRODRO, Congo -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- CONGO-ETHNIC-WARS-2 --
A nurse in the town of Drodro with a box of barbed arrowheads that
were removed from patients at a hospital there. The fighting,
although primitive, has killed at least 2,000 people and as many as
7,000. The worst attack occurred about 40 miles north of Bunia, in
the village of Blukwa. (Ian Fisher/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) DRODRO, Congo -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- CONGO-ETHNIC-WARS-1 --
Mandesi Bussi, a Hema who lost three of her five children in a
massacre by the Lendu, found one son, Singo Losukpa, alive among
the dead. The attack in January was reported to have killed 416
Hema. (Ian Fisher/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) TAMPA, Fla. -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- BBA-YANKS-POSADA --
Yankees cathcer Jorge Posada is a talented and hard-working
switch-hitter with power. Now that Joe Girardi is gone, having
signed with the Chicago Cubs, there is only Posada, coming off a
year in which he batted .245 and accumulated more passed balls (17)
than that of 26 teams. To be more effective, the 28-year-old
catcher must forge a better working relationship with the majority
of the Yankees' pitching staff. (Jon Adams/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) NEW YORK -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- BBN-METS-PIAZZA -- After a
rough-and-tumble 1999 season and postseason, Mets catcher Mike
Piazza, who will turn 32 on Sept.4, is ready to go again in 2000.
There are six springs left on Piazza's Mets contract, six more
years to produce as expected for a player with a seven-year,
$91million contract. (Barton Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT8) CHEYENNE, Wyo. -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- WEST-POLITICS-2 --
Gov. Jim Geringer, R-Wyo., says his region is overlooked. One
reflection of the region's scant influence is that, for the fifth
straight election cycle, not one of the presidential or vice
presidential debates is to be held in any of the eight states.
(Kevin Moloney/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) CHEYENNE, Wyo. -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- WEST-POLITICS-1 --
Gov. Jim Geringer, R-Wyo., says his region is overlooked. ``Any
kind of public debate would focus on policies of the West,'' he
says. Like protection of national forest lands. Who wouldn't be for
that? But if you don't talk about areas for grazing and areas for
logging, then you've not taken everybody into consideration. And
without debates, that part of it gets lost.'' (Kevin Moloney/The
New York Times)
</P>
