<P>
   (NYT30) NEW YORK -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- NY-ASSISTED-LIVING-2 --
Seated, from left, Janet Nemerofsky, Ben Siegel, Evelyn Marks and
James Alexander in the dining room at Atria Retirement and Assisted
Living in Riverdale, the Bronx. There is also a 24-hour snack bar.
Highly popular in suburbs all across the country, homes like these
were rare in New York City until two years ago, when developers
began trumpeting the city as an ideal new market. (Marilynn K.
Yee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) NEW YORK -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- NY-ASSISTED-LIVING-1 --
Janet Nemerofsky and Beryl Kadison play pool at Atria Retirement
and Assisted Living in Riverdale, the Bronx. Only 27 of the
building's 238 apartments have been rented since it opened five
months ago. (Marilynn K. Yee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT28) NEW YORK -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- JAZZ-INFLUENCE -- Robert
O'Meally, left, the founder and director of the Center for Jazz
Studies at Columbia University, and Wynton Marsalis, during an
inaugural lecture series at the center. ``Jazz is the best
soundtrack we have for contemporary American living,'' says
O'Meally, 51. (Nicole Bengiveno/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT27) NEW YORK -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- BKC-VILLANOVA-STJOHN --
Erick Barkley, in his return from a two-game suspension, gets down
to business with Villanova's Malik Allenin Madison Square Garden on
Saturday. He was an awful 6 of 16 from the field, missed four
3-pointers and, uncharacteristically, missed four free throws down
the stretch. But in the end, Barkley finished with 16 points and
St. John's prevailed, 78-75. (Michelle V. Agins/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- CAMPUS-WARNINGS -- It has
been a week since a young woman was slain at Columbia University
and her boyfriend committed suicide shortly afterward. As friends
mourn for Kathleen Roskot at Columbia University on Friday, the
murder of the sophomore - and two other recent attacks at other
area campuses - have underscored the problem of abusive
relationships. (Vic DeLucia/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) NEW YORK -- Feb. 12, 2000 -- MRSCLINTON-SENATE --
Hillary Rodham Clinton discussing health care Saturday at the
Scheuer Senior Center in Flushing, Queens. Though she repeated many
of the themes from her official announcement on Feb. 6., at every
turn the gatherings of Democratic officials and foot soldiers
responded as though they were hearing her remarks for the first
time. (Dith Pran/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT24) SANTA CLARITA, CA -- Feb. 13, 2000 -- CALIF-SPRAWL-3 --
The largest housing development ever approved by Los Angeles County
- the Newhall Ranch - will be set in the rolling hills marking its
border, beyond the Santa Clarita houses in the foreground. By 2025,
the state's population of 34 million is projected to grow by 18
million (a whole New York state); the Los Angeles region alone is
expected to swell by 6 million (or two Chicagos). (Monica
Almeida/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT23) SANTA CLARITA, CA -- Feb. 13, 2000 -- CALIF-SPRAWL-2 --
Stevenson Ranch, which borders the Newhall Ranch - the largest
housing development ever approved by Los Angeles County. To its
backers, Newhall Ranch is a sensitively planned community. But
critics point out that much of the demand for housing in the region
